# Brand assets (`public/`)

General `next/image` policy, `localPatterns`/`remotePatterns`, and SVG defaults: **`.cursor/rules/images.mdc`**.

Authoritative path constants: [`lib/site.ts`](lib/site.ts) (`FAVICON_ICO`, `APP_ICON_*`, `BRAND_*`, `DEFAULT_OG_IMAGE`). Import constants — never string literals.

## Asset taxonomy

| Constant | Purpose | Where used |
|---|---|---|
| `APP_ICON_192/512_PNG` | Transparent tab icon (both themes) | `metadata.icons` with `media: "(prefers-color-scheme: light\|dark)"` |
| `APP_ICON_MASKABLE_512_PNG` | PWA manifest only (`purpose: "maskable"`) | `app/manifest.ts` — do not swap into UI art |
| `BRAND_COMBINED_LOCKUP_PNG` / `BRAND_COMBINED_LOCKUP_DARK_PNG` | Full brand lockup, theme-aware | [`AfendaBrandLockup`](components/afenda-brand.tsx) — auth flows, dashboard shell, account/admin layouts, `not-found`/`error`/root `loading` |
| `BRAND_TYPOGRAPHY_LOCKUP_SVG` / `BRAND_WORDMARK_MONO_SVG` | Text-first wordmark | Text-forward branding surfaces |
| `DEFAULT_OG_IMAGE` | Default OG/Twitter share card | `metadata.openGraph.images` |

## Tab icons and metadata

- `metadata.icons` in [`app/layout.tsx`](app/layout.tsx): use typed `url`/`sizes`/`type` with `media: "(prefers-color-scheme: light|dark)"` — not `next-themes`.
- `/favicon.ico` is a real ICO in both `public/` and `app/` (App Router convention). Regenerate both via `pnpm icons:favicon` when `APP_ICON_512_PNG` changes.
- Root `generateMetadata` uses the **request host** for `metadataBase` so icon URLs resolve correctly on `*.vercel.app` and custom domains.
- `vercel.json` attaches CDN `Cache-Control` to `/favicon.ico` and `/icons/*` — bump filenames or reduce `max-age` when replacing assets in place.
- Avoid `app/icon.png` if it overrides themed `<link rel="icon">` entries.

## Composition rules

- Do not substitute Lucide or generic icons for product identity surfaces (nav brand, auth header).
- Prefer small focused components (`BrandMark` / `BrandLockup`) over one component with many boolean modes.
- Dark lockup raster is generated by [`scripts/knockout-dark-lockup-bg.mjs`](scripts/knockout-dark-lockup-bg.mjs) from `brand-guideline/dark-full-icon-bar.png`.

## OG and PWA

- `openGraph.images`: always include `width`, `height`, and `alt` matching the real asset dimensions.
- PWA manifest: use `purpose: "any"` vs `"maskable"` per asset — do not mix them.

## Process checklist (new files under `public/afenda-brand/` or `public/icons/`)

1. Update [`lib/site.ts`](lib/site.ts) with path constant.
2. Update [`app/layout.tsx`](app/layout.tsx) `metadata.icons` if tab art changes.
3. Run `pnpm icons:favicon` if the 512 source changed.
4. Extend `images.localPatterns` in [`next.config.ts`](next.config.ts) if a new `public/` subtree is used with `next/image`.
5. Add a short note under **Brand assets / Images** in [`AGENTS.md`](AGENTS.md).

The full Figma guideline raster (`afenda-figma-export-full-guideline.png`) is gitignored (GitHub 100 MB limit); keep it locally under `public/afenda-brand/brand-guideline/` for design reference only.
